sets.prompt:
When is the busy season for travel to {{[destination].tobo3bvu}}? 

If {{[dates].606jg3use}} is within the busy season, respond with only the value "1".

If {{[dates].606jg3use}} is not within the busy season, respond with only the value "0".

data.system: You are a information classifier. You ONLY respond with a 0 or 1 based on the information in the prompt.

children.text: What city are you travelling to and what do you like to do? The more details the better!
Hi, welcome to the Voiceflow travel assistant! Lets make a travel itinerary for you.
A users last response is automatically saved in the variable {last_utterance}
Want to create an open-ended question?
Voiceflow has multiple ways to recieve user input. You can use a  choice step to provide the user with immediate options.
You can also add an empty  choice step to create a prompt - which tells the assistant to stop and listen for user input.
This will allow a user to jump to any 'intent event' in your project. Learn more
here
The choice step lets a user type a response to go down a path.
On basic WhatsApp projects you can use the choice step to let a user move down a certain path.
Make sure to train your assistant (press prototype or 'r', then train). And you can type yes or no at this point to move down a path.
To use buttons on WhatsApp you have to use a webchat project with our API. Tutorial
here
Want to create jumping points in your conversation?
Intent events
are one of the most powerful features in Voiceflow. You can access them from the 'event' section in your step menu.

These intents can be global across your project or local to a specific topic. Whenever a user types the utterances included in the intent, they will be jumped to the intent wherever it is in your project.
This allows you to create advanced, non-linear conversations for your customers.
